column1188: Intelligent Tutoring Systems (ITS) are inherently complex, domain-oriented software systems which are frequently pointed out by researchers as suitable applications for the multi-agent approach. Developing and maintaining Multi-agent ITS are a hard task since it involves different stakeholders, with different expert and roles, such as developers, for developing new software features; domain experts, for managing ITS knowledge domain; authors, for customizing ITS execution for a given context; and users, which are not aware about ITS complexity and require a friendly user interface to interact with the system. Some works have been proposed to support the development of ITS, but they do not consider the stakeholders involved in the whole development and maintenance processes. In this project we present a software framework for designing, developing, and maintenance of Multi-agent ITS. This framework aims to be useful to ITS developers, domain experts, authors and users, providing a different view for each stakeholder, with different tools to support their activities. The focus here is more on developers and describe the framework architecture, design, and extension points, detailing how to customize them for specific domains.

column1266:
Economic development depends on highly skilled, educated individuals. Lower education level is linked to low income, poverty. In the UK, Higher Education is available to many high school graduates (~50% in 2011-12; The Guardian). In Brazil, numbers are much lower (< 20%; OECD). Pioneering efforts from academia & companies (incl. proposers) to support pupils from impoverished, underprivileged backgrounds to enter universities (to pass the intensive public exam ' ENEM'), are e-learning solutions. Still, initial data show typical distance learning problems: isolation, lack of customisation. The workshop invites UK, Brazil & international researchers towards solving the urgent, timely problem of access for children from impoverished backgrounds, via new, seamless personalisation, gamification, semantic & social interaction techniques for specific needs of the millions of candidates, based on (big) data analysis, user analytics, scalability. It dedicatedly promotes equal opportunities.
The workshop's main aim is to bring together researchers, practitioners, other stakeholders working or interested in the fields of educational technology, semantic web, Web 2.0, adaptivity, big data, learner analytics, NLP. We expect to discuss the merger of research and application directions, see their implementations and evaluations, encourage the transition towards concrete, large scale applications - such as in the Brazilian entrance to higher education field. Participants are expected to leave with a better knowledge of current research, to have fruitful brainstorming sessions, generate new ideas and new paths. Discussions results will be posted after the workshop on-line, as in previous workshops, and a special issue in a quality journal will be proposed (Valor aprox. R$ 170.000,00)

column1376: The main goal of this project is to investigate and to demonstrate the hypothesis that the integration of the Information retrieval field, Information extraction field, ontology creation and 3D visualization can solve the problem in displaying a complete global view of large information spaces in a limited screen, and the problem of searching and navigating through such large global views to find particular and relevant data items in meme dissemination. The specifics goals are: Given a set of terms, retrieval of relevant blogs post from blogosphere. Extraction of relevant attributes or metrics from unstructured data sets (Blog corpus). To develop sentimental analysis of these blog corpus and classify according to sentiment (Human feelings). To develop a Blog Ontology. To develop a Meme Transmission Path and a social network graph (taking on consideration the new FOAF format). To propose a new visualization scheme for navigating through the data. Exploring visualization techniques such as: overview, zoom, filtering, details on demand, relate, and history. To design and to implement a GUI prototype based on 3D visualization for this blogosphere. To create a user-experience design methodology (HCI) for 3D visualization. To investigate and to validate if the use of the graphical metaphor for interacting with computer can help to make visualization ubiquitous and to help people gain insights from large-scale collections of unstructured corpus for the study of meme dispersion.

column1820: O projeto Alagoas Histrica Digital tem por objetivo geral a preservao, digitalizao e difuso do acervo histrico eclesistico de Alagoas, presente no Arquivo da Arquidiocese de Macei. A metodologia utilizada ser a articulao interdisciplinar de conhecimentos histricos e da cincia da computao para a organizao e tratamento da documentao, construo de instrumentos de pesquisa, digitalizao e indexao atravs da criao de sistema para a gesto digital das fontes histricas e sua difuso. Alm disso, privilegiar-se- a escrita de artigos cientficos histricos e de cincia da computao para difuso cultural do acervo, e das metodologias utilizadas, como tambm para o incentivo ao fortalecimento de uma historiografia local sobre as temticas de histria de Alagoas, do Brasil e das Religies. O acervo compe-se de uma variedade de tipologias de fontes. Est dividido entre fundos de Administrao Eclesistica (cartas, ofcios, circulares, processos, administrao paroquial etc.), Manuscritos e livros de tombo (Visitaes, Compromissos de Irmandades, Livros de Batismo, Casamentos e bitos, c.1814-1980), Hemeroteca (Jornal O Semeador e boletins diversos, c.1913-2010), Biblioteca de obras raras (livros, revistas e peridicos, c.1890-1990), Pastorais e movimentos sociais leigos (relatrios, planejamentos, atas de reunies e encontros etc, c.1960-2000). Tal documentao abrange espacialmente toda a diocese de Macei, capital e as cidades do interior sob sua tutela. Temporalmente, vai-se do final do perodo colonial (1814), passando pelo Imprio e a Repblica (c.2006). A importncia deste acervo justifica-se na sua variedade e diversidade de assuntos e registros das mudanas sociais, econmicas, polticas e religiosas pelas quais passaram a cidade e o Estado no perodo indicado. Quer-se, por fim, contribuir para a universalizao do conhecimento, o desenvolvimento de habilidades e tcnicas especficas nas reas aqui interligadas, e para o incentivo e inovao (Valor aprox. R$ 60.000,00).

column2297: No mbito do projeto "IEB-TRANS - SISTEMAS VIRTUAIS DE ENSINO BASEADOS NA INTERNET PARA SUPORTE  EDUCAO E TREINAMENTO NA REA DA SADE", cabe  equipe da UCB a concepo e o desenvolvimento de um ambiente de visualizao volumtrica de estruturas biolgicas para o ensino de anatomia humana. Em termos metodolgicos, nos cabe a definio e implementao da interface grfica, e das rotinas de importao de modelos, dever ser implementada uma biblioteca de rotinas bsicas para a manipulao de estruturas de dados tpicos aos modelos de computao grfica. Com essas rotinas ser possvel executar as funes bsicas de manipulao de modelos grficos tridimensionais, como as transformaes geomtricas e o rendering, que  a apresentao do modelo tridimensional na tela considerando todas as suas propriedades tais como cor, textura, brilho, etc. A biblioteca grfica ser baseada no OpenGL e no C++. O OpenGL e o C++ so padronizadas e multi-plataforma. Alm disso, ser desenvolvido um mdulo educacional (Sistema Tutor) para a rea de anatomia ssea do crnio. .

column2340: Para o desenvolvimento de sistemas complexos, como pode ser caracterizado o desta proposta, precisamos cada vez mais envolver e deter a ateno dos usurios finais, que so bastante eclticos e de conhecimentos totalmente heterogneos. Ento, usamos a Inteligncia Artificial (IA) com a finalidade de desenvolver os esboos da criao artificial e s assim conseguimos uma interface homem-mquina adequada e capaz de atingir todos os nossos objetivos.  o uso criativo do computador associado  IA, bem como a outras tecnologias, isto , realidade virtual, robtica, telemedicina, banco de dados, pronturios eletrnicos, processamento de sinais e imagens e outras, que nos permite o desenvolvimento de aplicaes interessantes e fceis de manipular. Neste contexto, esta proposta visa a criao de um sistema dinmico, de grande utilidade, que atingir um grande universo de possveis usurios e que se adapta aos perfis de cada um, trazendo muita informao e conhecimento atravs de um ambiente virtual que simula um consultrio mdico e um ambiente de aprendizagem.
